Writing Challenge for thinkxlovexloud

Hey! A big thank you for helping me reach 1500 followers ❤️ To celebrate, I thought I’d do my first writing challenge!

Rules:

  • Open to everyone
  • Deadline is the end of July
  • Write for Chris Evans or Sebastian Stan (or any characters they’ve played in films)
  • Pick a prompt from the list below and then message/reply to let me know
  • Tag using #txlxlwritingchallenge or #thinkxlovexloudwritingchallenge

Prompts:

1. ‘I found this meme and it reminded me of you’

2. ‘Can you teach me how to play?’

3. ‘Say that again! I dare you’ @anti-endgame-ending

4. ‘There’s something in your hair. Let me get it out for you’ @twittytelly

5. ‘I can’t do this anymore. I need some space’ @thegetawaywriter

6. ‘I’ll explain later. I promise’

7. ‘Are you sure? I mean, we could get arrested for this’ @capsheadquaters

8. ‘Are you sure you want to put it there?’

9. ‘You trust me, don’t you?’ @cevansgirl

10. ‘Hold me closer. I can’t stand the noise’ @writingsofaninvisiblegirl

11. ‘Love is overrated’ @whiskey-cokenfanfic

12. ‘Just this one time. Please.’ @great-neckpectations

13. ‘Why do you keep looking over there? Who is it?’ @letstalkaboutsebbaby

14. ‘Does that feel good? Do you want me to carry on?’

15. ‘Wow, I can’t believe it. Are we really doing this?’ @if-n0t-l8ter-when

——————

My tag list (but it’s open to anyone):

summary: Are you ever afraid of meeting your fave and being disappointed? Cause I am. I try not to put anyone on a pedestal, even our...
question: Are you ever afraid of meeting your fave and being disappointed? Cause I am. I try not to put anyone on a pedestal, even our beloved Chris. I have my own idea of what he’s like, but I know I’m prob wrong. For a while I was part of the fandom that likened him to Steve Rogers, but I realized he’s not Steve. I also don’t think he’d want us to give him god-like worship. In the end, he’s a lot more like regular white men than most wanna accept. I’ll just keep my fantasies to myself lol 😂😭
answer:
Oh I’m definitely afraid lol

But I think for the most part when people meet celebs who act rudely when they’re usually not, is on a day when they’re not feeling their best

I always hear really nice things about people meeting my faves

But I feel you for sure!
